b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48525.htm)  [Next](sbe48527.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n10\\. Hence not in the way of destruction of bondage.\n\nIt thus appears that the text 'when all desires which once entered his heart\nare undone, then does the mortal become immortal, then he obtains Brahman ' (B\n_ri_. Up. IV, 4, 7), does not mean such immortality as would imply complete\ndestruction of the state of bondage.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 11. And to that very subtle body there belongs the\nwarmth](sbe48527.htm)\n\n"